                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding contemporary="Ethiopian false">
                                <decoNote xml:id="b1" type="bindingMaterial">
                                  The book is bound in <material key="wood">wooden</material> boards.
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="Boards">
                                  The boards are few millimeters larger than the leaves. The grain runs vertically.
                                  The external surface and the edges of the boards are polished and a finishing layer of dark colour has been added.
                                  The lower board has been repaired when it broke vertically in two halves which have been glued together.
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="SewingStations">4</decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b4">
                                  The main sewing is broken throughout. It consisted in a chainstitch sewing on four sewing stations (two pairs); periodic fold pattern; Z-plied thread.
                                  <locus target="#53"/> is stitched through the inner margin directly to <locus target="#54"/>.
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="Other">
                                  The separated bifolia are now crudely stitched to parchment or textile <term key="guard">guards</term> which have been placed around the quires.
                                </decoNote>
                            </binding>
